content: I think I'll start with "The Miracle of Mindfulness" by Thich Nhat Hanh, as I've heard great things about it. I'll also check out "The Self-Care Revolution" by Suzy Reading, as it seems like a practical guide to prioritizing my well-being. I'll try to read a little bit each day and reflect on what I've learned. By the way, I've been wearing my Apple Watch since January 15th, and it's been really helpful in tracking my daily activities and sleep.
